text: Yummy fried rice and succulent pork chop only $6.50 at this newly opened stall at Clementi West. Can try their Mala noodle too. Their chicken wings are huge and flavourful.
Love their fried rice, pork chop and chicken cutlet. It’s really nice and yummy! The 红油抄手 is also delicious! Had a good lunch with my friend! Do give it a try :)

Very generous with the amount of egg and shrimps. For $6.50 egg fried rice with shrimps, the portion is sizable. Whilst it cannot claim to have every grain coated with egg, the fluffy grains were well separated from each other, evidence of thorough frying of overnight left over rice.

Very nice. Must return to try their other items especially the spicy wantan noodle.
Really enjoyed this fried rice. Not too heavy and salty. Can finish it. Plus the toppings are really meaty. I love the wontons too.
Love the fried rice & spicy wantons. Tasty food at a affordable price! Conveniently located at Clementi. Worth the visit!
